The 2021 Auckland Classic tennis tournament has been scrapped because of  difficulties hosting during the coronavirus pandemic WELLINGTON - The 2021 Auckland Classic tennis tournament has been scrapped because of difficulties hosting during the coronavirus pandemic, organisers said on Tuesday. The New Zealand hardcourt tournament in early January is a warm-up for the Australian Open and has attracted top names in recent years, including this year's women's champion Serena Williams. READ: Aussie Open aspiring for up to half-full stadiums Tournament director Karl Budge said the COVID-19 crisis had created an uncertain environment that made it unfeasible to stage such a complex event. "We are obviously incredibly sad to share this news but safety has to be our priority," he said in a statement. Budge said organisers are committed to ensuring the tournament goes ahead in 2022.